Homme proved to be one of the best local acts at Chicago's Pitchfork Festival 
when they took the Blue Stage and kicked things off with their pitch-perfect 
alternating vocals, rock-inspired guitar riffs and pleasing melodies. Those pop
melodies gradually turn into noise rock jams while Macie Stewart and Sima Cunningham 
create harmonies that are a bit eerie and wonderfully unsettling. This performance, 
along with their 2015 self-titled release which contains six unique and intriguing 
songs, both promise amazing things to come.
